    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>How the Moot Board of Governors handles your information.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="content-block legal">
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: June 2026</p>

      <p>The Moot Board of Governors ("we", "us", "the Board") is a national association of student pre-law societies. This policy explains what personal information we collect through this website and how we use it. We follow the principles of Canada's <em>Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act</em> (PIPEDA).</p>

      <h3>1. Information we collect</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contact form:</strong> when you message us, we collect the name, email address, society, and message you submit. These are sent to us through Netlify Forms.</li>
        <li><strong>Representative &amp; society details:</strong> we publish the names and roles of board representatives and member-society contacts, with their consent.</li>
        <li><strong>Photos:</strong> we publish event and competition photos that may show identifiable people, taken at Board or member-society events.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> use advertising trackers, and we do not sell or rent personal information to anyone.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>2. How we use it</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>To respond to inquiries about membership, competitions, partnerships, or events.</li>
        <li>To coordinate national competitions and communicate with member societies.</li>
        <li>To promote the Board and its activities (e.g. publishing event photos).</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>3. Where it is stored</h3>
      <p>This site is hosted by Netlify, and contact-form submissions are processed by Netlify's form service, governed by Netlify's own privacy policy. Page content and photos are stored in the website's code repository on GitHub.</p>

      <h3>4. Photo removal &amp; your rights</h3>
      <p>You have the right to ask what personal information we hold about you, to correct it, or to have it removed. <strong>If you appear in a photo and want it taken down, contact us and we will remove it promptly.</strong> Requests can be made through our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>{% if site.email %} or by email at <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>{% endif %}.</p>

      <h3>5. Children</h3>
      <p>This site is aimed at university students and the general public. We do not knowingly collect information from anyone under 13.</p>

      <h3>6. Changes to this policy</h3>
      <p>We may update this policy from time to time. The "last updated" date above will always reflect the current version.</p>

      <h3>7. Contact</h3>
      <p>Questions about this policy or your information? Reach us through the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>{% if site.email %} or by email at <a href="mailto:{{ site.email }}">{{ site.email }}</a>{% endif %}.</p>

      <p class="legal-disclaimer"><strong>Note:</strong> The Board is an association of independent student organizations and is not affiliated with any single university. This policy is provided in good faith and is not legal advice.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
